b'Today we are celebrating with Brady and the @kentwood_petshotel team on the one-year anniversary of the day the team saved the golden retriever\xe2\x80\x99s life. During a PetsHotel visit last year, Brady was showing signs of Gastric Dilatation with Volvulus (GDV), otherwise known as a twisted stomach or \xe2\x80\x9cBloat.\xe2\x80\x9d Thankfully, the team\xe2\x80\x99s quick recognition of the GDV warning signs and action to take him to an emergency vet ended up saving his life. b'As people transition back to the office, pets who\xe2\x80\x99ve become used to having them at home may experience separation anxiety. It\xe2\x80\x99s important to spot the signs: dogs may chew furniture, dig holes and bark excessively, while cats may exhibit decreased appetite or obsessive grooming. Check out our stories today for tips that could help your pet deal with separation anxiety. :red_heart_selector: #fortheloveofpets'

b"When Korey and his wife moved into their first house, they knew it was time to get a dog. Korey had never had a dog, but his wife grew up with dogs her whole life and had wanted one for a while. They knew they wanted to adopt so they began looking around at local shelters. They were referred to @luckydogrescueaz in Phoenix so they took a look at available dogs on their website. That's when they saw Jada. Her description sounded perfect for a first-time pet parent like Korey. He knew they just had to meet her, so they decided to visit her. Jada was very playful and immediately took to them. Her foster mom told them another family was coming to meet her in a few minutes, so they needed to know if they wanted to adopt her, right then and there. They looked at each other and knew. She was the one.\n\nSince adopting Jada, they have become the happiest family of three. Jada loves to cuddle on the couch with them and follow them around wherever they go. They both say they can't imagine not having her and that their home would be so empty without her.  Stop by your local store to find your Jada during @PetSmartCharities National Adoption Weekend taking place Feb. 28 to Mar. 1. #iadopted (:camera:: @poemtoknowone)"
